Police have recovered singer Chris Evans' vehicle which had been stolen from him by thugs on Monday night. Kampala Metropolitan police spokesman, Luke Owoyesigyire, said Chris Evans' car was found in Kigaga zone, in Mutundwe, Lubaga division, Kampala. "We have recovered the vehicle reg number UAZ 399J dumped by the roadside in Mutundwe. It's now parked at Natete police station," Mr Owoyesigyire said. The Ndikusasulaki hit-maker was attacked by thugs in Lungujja, Mengo, who took off with his car after beating him to pulp. According to his manager Mr Godfrey Kayemba, Chris Evans' head was badly hit with hammers and is currently fighting for his life at Mengo Hospital.